Rave of the moment Asake will thrill fun lovers at the maiden event of Lagos luxurious palace Secret Palace Open Bar (SPOB) on July 20. Considered the most luxurious in terms of five-star luxury and entertainment, the Palace is acclaimed second to none. Hidden in the ultra-exclusive neighborhood of king of Elegushi, the palace boasts plush fittings and extravagantly royal finishes.   My battle with sickle cell, by Adekunle Gold     Baba Ijesha: Yomi Fabiyi’s estranged lover cancels…     Train your sons, Etinosa Idemudia begs parents   The maiden SPOB event takes off with a black carpet scheduled for 9pm while the main groove starts from 11pm to 1am. Owned by Seyi Ademoye better known as Sheyman, SPOB is best described as the “Buffet of Shots and Liquor mixes’ every Wednesday from 11pm to 1am. Other attractions include international exotic dancers from U.S A, Dominican Republic and South Africa. And of course the buffet service of shots and Liquor mixes where eligible guests can drink as much as they want for just a token.